<TITLE> Govt to sit with party leaders in bid to curb prices: adviser </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 17 (bdnews24.com)The caretaker government has said it will consider the opinions of political parties in its efforts to combat the spiralling prices of market essentials, an adviser said Thursday. The caretaker administration is expected to invite representatives of different political parties to discuss the matter soon. Commerce adviser Hossain Zillur Rahman told bdnews24.com: "The government has taken various steps to maintain the price of essentials within a tolerable level." "We have taken advice from experts at different levels of society in this matter, and as part of that process we will also speak with experts within the political parties," said Zillur. The commerce adviser invited Awami League leader and former commerce minister Tofail Ahmed to discuss the issue of price hikes at the ministry Thursday, although the meeting was postponed. "The meeting will be held in a few days, and we will sit with the experts of other political parties in phases," said the adviser. bdnews24.co
